The paper deals with computational complexity of graph problems, specifically related to vertex and component connectivity. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves graph theory (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) in its analysis. Additionally, the paper discusses results related to co-comparability graphs and interval graphs, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG).
